In this press conference, President Obama discusses his efforts to dig the US out of the recession and grow the economy. He talks about the policies of the previous decade that led to the recession and outlines his own principles for economic growth. He also discusses the need to pass a small business jobs bill that has been held up in the Senate. Additionally, he announces a change in his economic team, with Austan Goolsbee replacing Christina Romer as Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers. The President also addresses questions about the economy, the Middle East peace process, the war in Afghanistan, the issue of Guantanamo Bay, and the controversy surrounding the building of a mosque near Ground Zero. He reiterates the importance of capturing or killing Osama bin Laden and addresses concerns about the US justice system.